Package me.philcali.device.pool

Class BaseDevicePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.philcali.device.pool.BaseDevicePool
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, DevicePool
    @Immutable
public abstract class BaseDevicePool
extends Object
implements DevicePool
    The BaseDevicePool implements the DevicePool breaking down the control plane implementation into distinct components for flexible injection. Some components might represent both the ReservationService and ProvisionService control plane functions, for which they can be set simultaneously via the BaseDevicePool.Builder. The same is also true with ConnectionFactory and ContentTransferAgentFactory for generating Device. The BaseDevicePool implements the obtain method by exchanging complete Reservation detail for Host data path information to be used in generated Connection and ContentTransferAgent. The Device implementation is a BaseDevice.

      • provision

        public ProvisionOutput provision​(ProvisionInput input)
                          throws ProvisioningException
        Creates a provision request for this DevicePool implementation. It is important to know that the provisioning process is asynchronous. Some implementations may be able to fulfill the request immediately, and some may inform systems to acquire the necessary resources. This method is considered the entrypoint of the provisioning workflow.
